25 20-16-2603. Prohibition — Race-selection abortion.
26 (a) A physician or other person shall not intentionally perform or
27 attempt to perform an abortion with the knowledge that the pregnant woman is
28 seeking the abortion solely on the basis of the race of the unborn child.
29 (b) Before performing an abortion, the physician or other person who
30 is performing the abortion shall:
31 (1)(A) Ask the pregnant woman if she knows the race of the
32 unborn child.
33 (B) If the pregnant woman knows the race of the unborn
34 child, the physician or other person who is performing the abortion shall
35 inform the pregnant woman of the prohibition of abortion as a method of race
36 selection for children; and
