2 relating directly to the entire pregnancy history of the woman.
3 (B) An abortion shall not be performed until reasonable
4 time and effort is spent to obtain the medical records of the pregnant woman
5 as described in subdivision (b)(2)(A) of this section.
6 (c) If this section is held invalid as applied to the period of
7 pregnancy prior to viability, then the section shall remain applicable to the
8 period of pregnancy subsequent to viability.
